lor="off" border_color="#ffffff" border_style="solid"] Join us each <a href="http://heartofthehealer.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/THOTH-Wednesday-Night-Link-Up-new.pdf">Wednesday for our Pachakuti Mesa Tradition Link Up¬†</a> [/et_pb_blurb][/et_pb_column][/et_pb_row][et_pb_row admin_label="Row"][et_pb_column type="4_4"][et_pb_testimonial admin_label="Testimonial" author=" don Oscar Miro-Quesada" url_new_window="off" quote_icon="on" use_background_color="on" background_color="#60b9ba" background_layout="dark" text_orientation="center" quote_icon_color="#6b6b6b" use_border_color="off" border_color="#ffffff" border_style="solid"] ‚ÄúThe main purpose of our coming together is to open our hearts so fully to one another that even the slightest remnant of fear that is consciously or unconsciously part of our human experience shall be transformed by the power of unlimited Love into an experience of Communion with a sentient, compassionate, infinitely wise Universe. We are here to teach love by the way we live. As Pachakuti Mesa Carriers we are ‚Äúcultural transformers‚Äù awake to the primacy of consciousness with Creation.‚Äù [/et_pb_testimonial][/et_pb_column][/et_pb_row][et_pb_row admin_label="Row"][et_pb_column type="1_2"][et_pb_text admin_label="Text" background_layout="light" text_orientation="center" use_border_color="off" border_color="#ffffff" border_style="solid"]
<h3>SUYU:</h3>
Derived from the Inka culture of Peru, the use of the word Suyu refers to a territorial region consisting of individual ‚Äústates‚Äù that constitute a geomagnetically aligned field that sustains our planetary biosphere.

